template_id: openagreements-restrictive-covenant-north-dakota
name: Employee Restrictive Covenant (North Dakota)
category: non-compete
description: >-
  North Dakota-specific employee restrictive covenant agreement centered on
  confidentiality, trade secret protection, property return, non-disparagement,
  and a narrowly drafted anti-raiding employee non-solicitation covenant. Omits
  any employee covenant not to compete, any customer non-solicitation covenant,
  and any non-dealing covenant, because N.D. Cent. Code § 9-08-06 makes a
  contract that restrains a lawful profession, trade, or business to that extent
  void, and North Dakota case law treats post-employment customer solicitation
  and replacement restrictions as void with no statutory exception. It preserves
  only the covenants North Dakota law leaves enforceable — confidentiality and
  trade-secret protection under N.D. Cent. Code ch. 47-25.1, non-disparagement,
  property return, and a narrow anti-raiding employee non-solicitation covenant
  North Dakota case law treats as not void as a restraint of trade — each drawn
  to reach only Covered Employees the worker actually dealt with, keyed to
  Employee-initiated solicitation and a defined Restricted Period, so it
  protects the workforce and information rather than functioning as a restraint
  on competition. Includes North Dakota choice-of-law and forum language
  reflecting North Dakota public policy against enforcing a non-compete through
  a foreign choice-of-law or forum selection and N.D. Cent. Code § 28-04.1-03.
  Drafted as a starting point for licensed counsel review.
